{title: Sugar In Your Coffee}
{artist: Bill Anderson}
{composer: Written by Ray Griff}

[G]I came downstairs and found the mornin' [D7]paper by my plate
A glass of orange juice waitin' there for [G]me
I looked across the table and I [D7]saw the sweetest face
She smiled at me and then I heard her [G]say
Do you want sugar in your coffee [D7]honey on your toast
Or baby would you rather [G]that I hold you close
Do you want scrambled eggs and bacon a [C]bowl of shredded wheat
Do you want [D7]sugar in your coffee or lovin' warm and [G]sweet
I watched her as she moved and knew that she [D7]was heaven sent
I lived again sweet memories in my [G]head
I never knew real happiness or [D7]what it really meant
Until my baby turned to me and [G]said
Do you want sugar in your coffee [D7]honey on your toast
Or baby would you rather [G]that I hold you close
Do you want fingertips to touch you and [C]kisses on your cheek
Do you want [D7]sugar in your coffee or lovin' warm and [G]sweet
repeat #4